id: pm-7071
title: Intentional package CommandError outcomes create high-severity Sentry issues (PM-CLI-16)
description: "Typed package/extension CommandError values with an explicit numeric exitCode represent handled command outcomes, but sentryCaptureCliError currently records generic-failure exit code 1 as an exception. Preserve raw Error capture while treating explicit CommandError control flow like PmCliError so telemetry retains the failed command without creating unresolved error groups. Duplicate check: exact PM-CLI-16 and verify-release title searches across all statuses found only historical evidence comments, not a canonical active defect item."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-07-13T23:36:29.498Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T02:41:46.928Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T02:41:46.220Z"
author: codex-root
acceptance_criteria: Sentry capture skips only Error values named CommandError with an explicit numeric exitCode; raw Error and untyped CommandError values remain captured; command-finish telemetry retains the nonzero outcome; focused regressions and the live Sentry gate pass.
parent: pm-5oj5
risk: low
confidence: high
reporter: codex-root
severity: medium
environment: pm-cli 2026.7.13; Node v26.4.0; Linux; live handled Sentry PM-CLI-16 exitCode=1
repro_steps: "Run a package command that intentionally returns CommandError with numeric exitCode 1, such as a verify-release validation failure. Before the fix sentryCaptureCliError records it as an exception."
resolution: Sentry capture now treats only typed CommandError values with numeric exitCode as handled package control flow while preserving capture for raw and untyped failures.
expected_result: Typed handled CommandError outcomes remain in command telemetry without creating unresolved error-level Sentry groups.
actual_result: "Current-head typed CommandError suppression is covered and correct. A new handled event was traced to an external media-server pm-ops consumer still on published pm-cli 2026.7.13; PM-CLI-16 was resolved and the live gate reports critical=0, high=0, telemetry error rate 0.27%, and zero missing error-code rows. Host-specific provenance was audited-redacted from current metadata and history, whose hash chain verifies cleanly."
component: Sentry CLI error classification and package runtime
regression: false
customer_impact: Expected package validation outcomes polluted Sentry and could block daily releases.
